>QOTT: What origin story do you prefer for anthros? (i.e. genetically modified, magic, they were always there, etc)
It depends on the setting.
The idea of anthropomorphic animals seemingly design to serve and satisfy human men is absurd and fantastical, but, like any premise, it can work in the right context. In a fantasy with an original world and history it's easy to believe that anthros have always existed. However, in a modern setting meant to resemble our own, this would bring up so many questions and make it difficult to believe what's being presented. In this case, a light revision of history or small leap into the future with a more plausible explanation would be best, such as genetic engineering.
Genetic engineering is my favorite origin for anthros. It demonstrates the absolute power and control humanity has over the anthro. They aren't natural creatures. They're tools- toys. To deny this is delusional. Every bovine anthro knows they're born to provide milk and meat for their human masters. Every feline anthro knows they're born to provide company and comfort for their human masters. Every bunny girls know deep in their core they're only good for dumping a hot load in their holes.
Although, one origin I'd like to see more of is an inter-dimensional one where humans have pierced the fabric between realities and capture the natives to have them serve back home.
