Eras:
(??? – 1124 B.C.) Ancient Era
From the earliest pre-recorded history, up until the formation of the human empire on Panagea. During this Era, humans were the first to shift from hunter-gatherers to farmers, and settled the first proper civilizations– which would eventually unify into the Empire of Humanity. From here on out, evolution will slowly capitalize on their interbreeding with other anthro species, adapting them to be genetically predisposed to appeal to anthros as superior mates, as an evolutionary strategy.
(1123 B.C. – 541 B.C.) Early Imperial Era
–Empire of Humanity is formed
–All other human settlements are unified into the Empire
–A prosperous anthro slave trade begins, paternalist traditions of human masters and anthro slaves/pets form
–The countless anthro tribes surrounding the Empire are frequently raided, conquered, or vasalised
–The Hunter's Lodge is formed, a guild of those most passionate about hunting anthros for sport or slaves that sponsors and regulates the trade.
–War of Wolven Aggression (Cottonwind Pact), a large number of anthro tribes unite to attack the Empire of Humanity
–Firearms developed, limited by scarcity of niter
–The Great Call to Hunt begins to cull out of control anthro overpopulation in many wild areas of Panagea
–Generations of domesticated anthro women breeding exclusively with human men creates the first domesticated species offshoots (dogs, cats, etc.)
(542 B.C. – 1 B.C.) Late Imperial Era
–Human explorers land on the shores of the High Egyptian Empire in Nephir, first contact with another continent.
–Empire of Humanity enter into slave trading agreements with the Pharoah-Queen of High Egypt, Neithhotep. Other Nepherite civilizations such as the Nubian Empire and the Sobekhanate are also discovered.
–Human explorers discover Zyriatt, war with the natives and invade.
–The first Human Incursion War in Nephir begins against High Egypt
–Euradian explorers discover Nephir, establish a couple of colonies
–Shaian Explorers discover Panagea and the Empire of Humanity, cautious trade begins
–Human colonists land in Euradia, establish colonies.
–Second Human Incursion War on Nephir begins
–Human invasion into Euradia begins
–Internal issues, famines, and a Shaian ban on Imperial trade cause the Empire's expansion to halt
–Human colonies in Euradia are cut off from the Empire due to joint Euradian-Shaian blockade agreements
(1 A.C – 262 A.C.) Dark Ages
Unknown events cause the decline of the Empire of Humanity. No human presence remains on foreign continents, save for isolated colonies in Euradia. When historical records re-emerge, human population in Panagea is noticeably reduced, anthro population even more so.
(263 A.C – 1259 A.C.) Reformation Era
Humans re-expand throughout Panagea, and large multi-species anthro civilizations flourish on the other continents
(1260 A.C – 1758 A.C.) Renaissance Era
–Global trade flourishes between Euradia, Zyriatt, Nephir, and Shaia.
–Predator/Prey wars begin in Euradia
–Humans from Pangea cross landbridges with Euradia and Zyriatt, have first contact with foreign anthros since Late Imperial times. Humans are delighted to rediscover the anthros they are traditionally so fond of, and excited to enter the global world stage. Anthro nations are notably less enthusiastic to see the warmongers slaver race of ancient times.
–The lost human colonies on Euradia are rediscovered by the rest of the continent, having largely forgotten their original heritage and instead forming a sort of bizarre syncreticism with a native group of the newly sapient pokemon species of anthros.
(1759 A.C. – 1999 A.C.) Industrial Era
