In the world I’m creating, females Anthros can be impregnated almost year round, with mammalian Anthros following a very similar estrous cycle to that of a Human female. However, unlike Human females, female mammalian Anthros also go through seasonal periods of heightened reproductivity, in which they become not only extremely fertile, but also more likely to conceive twins, triplets, and even on rare occasions quadruplets (for some select species).
The exact time of such periods (known simply as ‘heat’) vary from species to species, with some even experiencing it multiple times a year. This ‘heat’ can last anywhere from a few days (if treated) to a month (if left untreated), with some species experiencing multi-month long periods.
Sadly, due to stereotypes brought forth by Human written smut novels, many Humans and non-mammalian Anthros have a fetishized view of this reproductive curse, with many assuming that this period is highly enjoyable amongst female mammalian-Anthros. This however could not be further from the truth.
In reality, while few may have a positive experience with ‘heat’, for most female’s this period is one of extreme discomfort, brought on by not only the frequent mood swings and oppressive sexual drive, but also from the almost painful increase in sexual sensitivity. This sensitivity not only impacts the Anthro’s ability to carry out everyday tasks, but also effect their sleep patterns which can lead to insomnia and exhaustion.
While this unfortunate period of time effects the females experiencing it, it also negatively effects societies as a whole, and can pose a noticeable strain on any business, Government, or company whom may possess a large number of female individuals. And in no other group is this risk as present as it is within the Royal Regnun military.
The Royal Regnun military, a large military made up mostly of canines, is one of the few militaries in the world of Nanetae that allows females to serve alongside males within mixed-sex units. This of course poses a risk to unit cohesion, as large numbers of soldiers, sailors, and marines could possibly be temporarily knocked out of service for upwards of a month if left unchecked. This makes dealing with heat cycles a top priority.
While new medicines have been created to help combat the effects of heat cycles, they remain extremely expensive and have a good amount of risk involved in taking them. As such most servicewomen are only able to deal with their heat cycles manually through sexual contact with males. However, such activities are forbidden within the ranks, and violators are subject to harsh discipline. Due to this, servicewomen are forced to turn to non-military partners to help soothe their afflictions.
Although such relationships are easy for those lucky enough to be stationed on the home island, who can visit or find mates, these relationships are rather tricky for those stationed or deployed away from home, where finding a fellow canine to mate with may be nigh impossible. This issue has lead to the development of a certain kind of culture, in which servicewomen indulge themselves with male locals regardless of species, most of whom being male prostitutes.
In no other land is such culture as common and catered towards as the nearby and currently occupied Human-majority island nation of Terratilis. On this island an entire industry has formed around soothing the inflammations caused by the ever reliable heat cycles of the female canine occupiers.
Once heat begins, female servicewomen are granted a one week pass in which they surrender their weapons and equipment to their local service stations armory before being allowed to travel to their nearest ‘relief village’. Upon arrival they will pay the fee before being united with the ‘relief worker’ of their choice. Such relief workers mostly consist of young men in search of extra money, with the most common of species involved being Human. Such relief workers are in extremely high demand, as most males are unwilling to do the job, and it’s not unheard of servicewomen reserving males months in advance.
Once united the pair will take up temporary residence within either an on-site brothel or a small pre-built house, the rooms of which being pre-stocked with food and drink along with access to baths, kitchens, and toilets.
The pair will remain together in an almost non-stop act of passion until either the female runs out of time on her pass, or her heat is finally cured. Once this is done the pair will say their farewells and will seperate.
Upon arrival back to their service station, the servicewoman will either be given another week pass, if her heat as not yet been fully treated, or medication to prevent any possible pregnancies caused by the activities. Such medication however are not 100% effective, and few find themselves dismissed from the military and sent back home with a hybrid growing inside of them, abortion not being allowed due to state-mandated religious reasons.

