>A single human spacer happens by the curious world and makes contact
>And what a wild reception he gets.
>His presence smashes the dopamine buttons in the brains of countless anthro species. Nearly all of them crave human physical affection on a primal level, and their animalistic instincts can surface because of it, making them act silly or needy.
