>how often do married furry women have anonymous breeding sex with human men they (at least try to) pull off the street?
Depends on the population ratio, but humans in general take 3-4 anthro females for themselves. However, the male anthros are not guaranteed to be cucked as about 3% of anthro females in mixed species urban environments stay loyal (read, don't pursue human males, this doesn't mean they won't bend to human men) and up to 11% in rural mixed species environments won't. Excluded from data are areas where there are no humans and a number of examples in which humans were barely present, however, even in these extreme situations where anthro females outnumbered human males in ratios of about 50:1, the ratio of loyal anthro females never exceeded 15%.
>what is the real chance that an anthro husband is actually the father to "his" children?
Genetic studies again show a wide variety of variances based upon population ratios, however, in case of a anthro female that at any point pursued regular contact with a human, there is almost a 95% chance at least one of her children will be sired by a human and a 60% that the majority of the children will be of human origin. The reasons for this are primarily biological as anthro females will subconsciously seek to be impregnated by humans when they are most fertile.
However, even in the case of the anthro females that don't seek regular contact with humans, but merely preside in the same environment, the ratio falls down to 50%.

