>with enough trial and error, he learned the xeno's stopped any and all attempts at violence or resistance provided they were bound to a certain degree and a certain level of tightness
>when they had a specific level of freedom, they turned dangerous
>eventually, he found what he considered to be the turning point, where the switch inside them flipped
>head strapped, chest strapped, hips strapped, arms strapped in three locations, legs strapped in three locations, and two straps holding down the tail
>if he loosened one leg strap enough for the leg to move a bit, the xeno promptly spat and snarled and attempted to break out
>if he tightened that one strap back down, the xeno relaxed and would just passively lay there
>it was disturbing to think there was another alien species out there somewhere with the technology to create other species
>much less an alien species that would use that power just to create an entire race that existed solely to be tightly tied up
>a race that would react with murderous rage when not tied

>Breaking news!
>(Michael Bay directed music intro)
>Recent studies suggest human consumption of breastmilk from snakes, known colloquially as "snilk", can cause addiction, leading to excessive consumption of this substance and extensively biased preference for snake partners and snake products by humans.
>Other anthros are worried that the recent surge in snilk consumption will lead to "a significant decrease in ethnic diversity", with snakes dominating the polls as the humans main partner. >Molly of the "mans best friend" party, accuses The scale party of "deliberately tampering" with their genetic code to produce an "excessively and illegally addictive substance"
>Lanessa, leader of the scale partly refutes any involvement direct or indirect in the snilks effects, claiming that the results of genetic splicing was "purely coincidental" And concludes her rebuttal by stating that "dogs bark at anything which passes by their masters home."
>A growing community of anthros are engaging in conspiracy theories, frequently believing that snakes and reptiles in general are brainwashing humans to prefer only reptiles for slaves. Some have begged their human masters of wearing tin foil around their tounge to protect them from "vile substances".
